{"id": "1441164867976564808", "channel_id": "1441164867976564808", "type": 0, "author_id": "298919354077151232", "author_name": "josephbroseph", "author_bot": false, "content": "It seems the replay goes either too fast and/or does not capture the precise order of cards played due to some kind of lag or delay, which you can see as sprite animations are triggered after plays that do not belong to that unit (screen recording attached, examples below).\n\nI played Sanga's Beauty's Mark first, then her Rouse, then Caecus' defense, but the replay shows Caecus' sprite animation after I play Sanga's Rouse and does not display her Rouse animation until after Posse is triggered and a Caecus defense card is played. Another example, Salvador's End of Suffering card is played *before* Posse is triggered but his animation triggers *after* Sanga's delayed Rouse post-Posse.\n\nThanks in advance for taking a look :-)", "timestamp": "2025-11-20T20:34:40.074000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1441164869897289789", "filename": "Replay_Bug.mp4", "content_type": "video/mp4", "size": 37140051, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1441164867976564808/1441164869897289789/Replay_Bug.mp4?ex=69cc2fe0&is=69cade60&hm=bb2df54242b6cee8f0359f0e7f98359dca98da487b13b3888769429b4f90ec1a&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1441164867976564808", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "💭「Processing」Replay feature displaying incorrect card play order", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168893200044183"]}
